{
    "Description": "<h3>Usage</h3><pre class=\"ql-syntax\" spellcheck=\"false\">Node:trimLWS()\n</pre><ul><li><code><strong>Node</strong></code>: A node containing a string value. Only leading (left-side) spaces will be removed.</li></ul><p><br></p><h3><strong>Notes</strong></h3><ul><li>Does not modify the original node—returns a new trimmed string.</li><li>Trailing white space (on the right side) is <strong>not</strong> affected.</li><li>Useful for formatting user input or normalizing data from HL7, XML, etc.</li></ul><p><br></p><h3><strong>Returns</strong></h3><ul><li>A string with leading white space trimmed. <em><u>(string)</u></em></li></ul><p><br></p><h3>Example</h3><pre class=\"ql-syntax\" spellcheck=\"false\">local Xml = xml.parse{data = \"&lt;value&gt;&nbsp; &nbsp;data&nbsp; &nbsp;&lt;/value&gt;\"}\nlocal Clean = Xml.value:trimLWS()\n-- Returns: 'data&nbsp; &nbsp;'\n</pre><ul><li>This example demonstrates trimming a node value from the left side only.</li></ul>",
    "Name": "node:trimLWS",
    "Parameters": null,
    "ParameterTable": false,
    "SummaryLine": "Trims white space from the left of a string."
}